My traveling companions were a few English and French tourists and agoodish bunch of gloomy officials from Soviet trade missions. Once insidethe aircraft, a certain illusion of cheap unreality enveloped me--to lingerabout me for the rest of my trip. It was a very warm day in June and thefarcica